## Phase 1: Foundation & Architecture Hardening

**Goal**: Transform the prototype into a production-grade base that all future phases build on.
**Duration**: 3 weeks · **Priority**: 🔴 Critical (blocks everything)

### 1.1 Database & Migration Infrastructure

#### [NEW] `standalone/alembic/` — Migration system
- Install Alembic, configure `alembic.ini` and `env.py`
- Generate initial migration from existing models
- All future schema changes go through Alembic (no more `create_all`)

#### [MODIFY] [models.py](file:///Users/utilisateur/Desktop/turbo-octo-robot/standalone/app/models.py)
- Add `updated_at` column to all models (auto-set on change)
- Add soft-delete (`is_deleted`, `deleted_at`) to all models
- Add `tenant_id` column to all models (white-label multi-tenancy prep)
- Add UUID primary keys alongside integer IDs (API uses UUIDs, DB uses ints)
- Add proper indexes for query performance

#### [MODIFY] [db.py](file:///Users/utilisateur/Desktop/turbo-octo-robot/standalone/app/db.py)
- Add connection pooling configuration
- Add async engine support (`create_async_engine`)
- Add session middleware for request-scoped sessions
- PostgreSQL-only (remove SQLite fallback for production)

### 1.2 Service Layer & Architecture

#### [NEW] `standalone/app/services/` — Business logic layer
- Extract all business logic from routers into service classes
- Pattern: Router → Service → Repository → DB
- Services: `ContactService`, `CompanyService`, `DocumentService`, `AuthService`

#### [NEW] `standalone/app/repositories/` — Data access layer
- Generic CRUD repository with pagination, filtering, sorting
- Soft-delete aware queries
- Tenant-scoped queries

#### [MODIFY] All routers in [routers/](file:///Users/utilisateur/Desktop/turbo-octo-robot/standalone/app/routers/)
- Thin routers that delegate to services
- Consistent error handling with structured error responses
- Request/response logging middleware

### 1.3 Testing Infrastructure

#### [NEW] `standalone/tests/` — Complete test suite
- `conftest.py` with test database, fixtures, factories
- `tests/unit/` for service logic
- `tests/integration/` for API endpoint tests
- `tests/factories/` with model factories (factory_boy or similar)
- Target: 80%+ coverage from day one

#### [NEW] [standalone/pyproject.toml](file:///Users/utilisateur/Desktop/turbo-octo-robot/standalone/pyproject.toml) updates
- Add dependencies: `alembic`, `factory-boy`, `pytest-asyncio`, `pytest-cov`, `celery`, `redis`

### 1.4 Async Task Queue

#### [NEW] `standalone/app/tasks/` — Background task system
- Celery + Redis for async job processing
- Task types: email sending, report generation, data enrichment, scheduled jobs
- Task status tracking API

### 1.5 Configuration & Environment

#### [MODIFY] [config.py](file:///Users/utilisateur/Desktop/turbo-octo-robot/standalone/app/config.py)
- Environment-based config (dev/staging/production)
- Secrets management (vault-ready)
- Feature flags system for progressive feature rollout

### Phase 1 Deliverables
- ✅ Alembic migrations working
- ✅ Service layer pattern established
- ✅ Test suite running with >80% coverage on existing code
- ✅ Async task queue operational
- ✅ Multi-tenant schema ready

