## Verification Plan

### Automated Testing (per phase)

Each phase includes its own test suite. Run all with:
```bash
cd standalone
pip install -e ".[dev]"
pytest tests/ -v --cov=app --cov-report=html
```

### Integration Testing
```bash
# Start all services
docker compose up -d

# Run integration tests against live API
pytest tests/integration/ -v

# Run E2E tests (Phase 13)
cd frontend && npx playwright test
```

### Manual Verification
- **After each phase**: Trigger all new API endpoints via Swagger UI at `http://localhost:8000/docs`
- **After Phase 9**: Full visual walkthrough of all frontend views in Chrome
- **After Phase 12**: White-label test — create new tenant, customize branding, verify isolation
- **After Phase 13**: Complete demo flow — create company → add contacts → create deal → move through pipeline → generate invoice → record payment → view P&L report

> [!TIP]
> Each phase should be merged as a separate PR with its test suite passing before moving to the next phase. This prevents accumulation of technical debt.

